Capital Growth Management LP Invests $35.84 Million in Banco Bradesco SA (BBD)


					Posted by Joanna Charbonneau on Jul 6th, 2017 // No Comments




Capital Growth Management LP bought a new position in shares of  Banco Bradesco SA (NYSE:BBD) during the first quarter, according to its most recent disclosure with the SEC. The firm bought 3,500,000 shares of the bank’s stock, valued at approximately $35,840,000. Banco Bradesco SA comprises approximately  1.6% of Capital Growth Management LP’s holdings, making the stock its 25th largest position. Capital Growth Management LP owned 0.06% of Banco Bradesco SA as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
Other large investors have also modified their holdings of the company. Vanguard Group Inc. increased its stake in shares of  Banco Bradesco SA by 5.3% in the first quarter. Vanguard Group Inc. now owns 32,806,678 shares of the bank’s stock worth $335,940,000 after buying an additional 1,658,539 shares in the last quarter.  Banco Santander S.A. increased its stake in shares of  Banco Bradesco SA by 496.4% in the first quarter. Banco Santander S.A. now owns 100,600 shares of the bank’s stock worth $913,000 after buying an additional 83,731 shares in the last quarter.  Koch Industries Inc. purchased a new stake in  Banco Bradesco SA during the first quarter valued at $114,000.  Baillie Gifford & Co. increased its stake in  Banco Bradesco SA by 12.4% in the first quarter. Baillie Gifford & Co. now owns 15,633,626 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $160,088,000 after buying an additional 1,720,966 shares during the period.  Finally, Massachusetts Financial Services Co. MA increased its stake in  Banco Bradesco SA by 55.2% in the first quarter. Massachusetts Financial Services Co. MA now owns 3,852,696 shares of the bank’s stock valued at $39,450,000 after buying an additional 1,370,923 shares during the period. 2.73% of the stock is currently owned by hedge funds and other institutional investors. 


 Get Banco Bradesco SA alerts:



Shares of Banco Bradesco SA (NYSE:BBD) traded down 1.28% during mid-day trading on Thursday, reaching $8.47. The company had a trading volume of 14,413,485 shares. Banco Bradesco SA has a 12-month low of $6.78 and a 12-month high of $10.37. The company has a market capitalization of $51.54 billion, a P/E ratio of 9.65 and a beta of 1.76. The firm has a 50-day moving average of $8.54 and a 200-day moving average of $8.94. 





Banco Bradesco SA (NYSE:BBD) last released its quarterly earnings data on Thursday, April 27th. The bank reported $0.27 earnings per share (EPS) for the quarter, beating the consensus estimate of $0.24 by $0.03. The company had revenue of $13.25 billion during the quarter. Banco Bradesco SA had a net margin of 9.08% and a return on equity of 17.32%.  On average, equities analysts anticipate that  Banco Bradesco SA will post $0.92 earnings per share for the current fiscal year. 
The business also recently disclosed a special dividend, which will be paid on Monday, July 24th. Shareholders of record on Thursday, July 6th will be given a $0.057 dividend. This represents a yield of 0.91%. This is a boost from Banco Bradesco SA’s previous special dividend of $0.01. The ex-dividend date of this dividend is Monday, July 3rd. Banco Bradesco SA’s payout ratio is 76.87%. 
